The paper discusses path-planning algorithms for robotic applications, which are typically studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of convolutional neural networks to learn search heuristics from environment images suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the real-time constraints of the problem may also indicate a connection to control systems (cs.SY).
